300
00:17:30,340 --> 00:17:31,269
Rym: It's the same old Mafia.

301
00:17:32,394 --> 00:17:34,090
Rym: It has a different set of roles.

302
00:17:34,492 --> 00:17:35,189
Rym: What are the roles?

303
00:17:35,491 --> 00:17:39,790
Rym: It has the angel and the archangel, like before, and other basic roles.

304
00:17:40,310 --> 00:17:46,548
Rym: Then it has the drunk, who one night can flip his role with someone else and no one gets to see but him.

305
00:17:47,290 --> 00:17:49,450
Scott: So the person who got flipped doesn't know what they are now?

306
00:17:49,470 --> 00:17:50,949
Rym: Yeah, they don't know what they are anymore.

307
00:17:51,115 --> 00:17:51,344
Rym: Uh-oh.

308
00:17:51,831 --> 00:17:56,150
Rym: And someone else, the troublemaker, picks two other people and swaps their roles all so secretly.

309
00:17:57,332 --> 00:17:58,229
Scott: But he can't swap his own.

310
00:17:58,490 --> 00:18:00,330
Rym: Now, a normal Mafia, that would be bullshit.

311
00:18:02,013 --> 00:18:03,350
Rym: Here's why this is interesting.

312
00:18:03,410 --> 00:18:05,870
Rym: This Mafia has one night and one day.

313
00:18:06,687 --> 00:18:06,749
Scott: Oh.

314
00:18:07,411 --> 00:18:12,089
Rym: One night happens, everyone does their secret shit, the Mafia recognize each other, everything happens.

315
00:18:12,750 --> 00:18:19,708
Rym: Then you all wake up, you decide, you vote with Zap style on who to lynch.

316
00:18:20,956 --> 00:18:22,670
Rym: And there's some rules for how many people you play.

317
00:18:22,830 --> 00:18:27,050
Rym: And basically, all the people who meet the threshold from the one point get killed.

318
00:18:28,774 --> 00:18:33,729
Rym: If only Mafia people get killed, or depending on the number of players, if any Mafia people get killed, the humans win.

319
00:18:34,711 --> 00:18:35,888
Rym: Otherwise, the Mafia win.

320
00:18:37,071 --> 00:18:41,610
Rym: It was the experience of you've got one day and there's a timer.

321
00:18:41,751 --> 00:18:42,769
Rym: You've got five minutes.

322
00:18:43,931 --> 00:18:50,190
Rym: So the game is everyone trying to logic it out and everyone else trying to, you're trying to figure out who would change what.

323
00:18:50,310 --> 00:18:51,749
Rym: It's almost like a timed logic puzzle.

324
00:18:54,192 --> 00:19:02,969
Rym: I was admonished because my strategy was to just lie and be super crazy in the first minute just to throw everyone off balance and try to figure out who was lying or not.

325
00:19:03,230 --> 00:19:03,987
Rym: But it worked really well.

326
00:19:05,891 --> 00:19:12,190
Rym: I'm going to explore this concept a little further and see if this is actually worth playing before I actually convince you to play it once with me.

327
00:19:12,270 --> 00:19:15,970
